Class Search

  • Object

  • public class Search

    • Field Detail

      • pageList

        public static List<Page> pageList
        Parsed pages. We will read in the list we made in the Crawler class and save it to this global static variable.

      • wordList

        public static List<Word> wordList
        List of Word objects. We will read in the list we made in the Crawler class and save it to this global static variable.

      • resultSet

        public static List<Result> resultSet
        List of Results. This will be shared by the threads. This list must be designed to be resilient to double counting by competing threads. Take a look at the Synchronizing Lists section of the handout for information on how to handle this.

        Word List File Path

      • nullCheck

        public void nullCheck()
        Utility method to check if we have not read in our lists from file. If we haven't, call the setup() method.

      • sort

        public void sort()
        Method to sort our ArrayList of Results by their score. Since the Result List is global, we don't need to pass it as a parameter or return it - we can simply access it within the method.
